.TH "ubifs_replace_cat" 9 "ubifs_replace_cat" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ubifs_replace_cat \- replace lprops in a category list or heap.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ubifs_replace_cat
.BI "(struct ubifs_info *c "  ","
.BI "struct ubifs_lprops *old_lprops "  ","
.BI "struct ubifs_lprops *new_lprops "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
UBIFS file-system description object
.IP "old_lprops" 12
LEB properties to replace
.IP "new_lprops" 12
LEB properties with which to replace
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
During commit it is sometimes necessary to copy a pnode (see dirty_cow_pnode)
and the lprops that the pnode contains. When that happens, references in
category lists and heaps must be replaced. This function does that.
